Description: A sherd of red pottery, from the shoulder of a Samian transport amphora. The exterior bears part of incised mark, made during production. Possibly from the same vessel as 23768.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 21, dry well south-west to the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: Johnston in Villing, A. and Schlotzhauer, U. (eds), Naukratis: Greek Diversity in Egypt, BM Research Publication 162, London., p. 28, Table 1, no. 10.
The Findspot number 21 has been scratched into the object. See also Boston, MFA, 87.626 (Petrie, ibid., p. 64 § 61, pl. xxxiii, 10.a), London, BM, EA 23751 (deacc.), London, PM, UC 19248.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 64, 66 § 61, pl. xxxiii, 10.d)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.115, p.128, p.215, p.224, pl.66)
